cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the interpretation of internal representations of deep neural networks trained for classification of diseased tissue in 2D mammograms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an expert-in-the-loop interpretation method, which involves expert radiologists, indicating that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses the use of CNNs, which is a popular machine learning technique, indicating that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the explanatory descriptions produced by the trained CNN models, indicating that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
